  • Place soy sauce, brown sugar, sherry, dried onion, cinnamon, olive oil, and a touch of garlic powder in a large resealable plastic bag. Seal, and shake to mix.
  • Place pork in bag with marinade, seal, and refrigerate for 6 to 12 hours.
  • Preheat grill or smoker for indirect heat.
  • Place tenderloins on grill, and keep marinade.
  • Cook until 140F.
  • While the pork is cooking, boil the marinade for 10 minutes to use as sauce.
  • Slice into medallions, drizzle with marinade, and serve.

  • 1/4 cup soy sauce
  • 1/4 cup packed brown sugar
  • 2 tablespoons sherry
  • 1 1/2 teaspoons dried minced onion
  • 1 teaspoon ground cinnamon
  • 2 tablespoons olive oil
  • 1 pinch garlic powder
  • 2 (3/4 pound) pork tenderloins
